HEADWORD: Water-withe
<hw>Wa"ter-withe`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A vinelike plant (<spn>Vitis Caribaea</spn>) growing in parched
districts in the West Indies, and containing a great amount of sap which
is sometimes used for quenching thirst.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterwork</ent>⟦br⟧
